And just food for thought
here, what I noticed

00:09:49.880 --> 00:09:54.812 align:middle line:10%
is that in this 16th century
image of the Transfiguration

00:09:54.812 --> 00:09:59.050 align:middle line:10%
from Crete, we see Jesus
in his light body form

00:09:59.050 --> 00:10:01.440 align:middle line:10%
with the gateway behind them,
and he's got these three

00:10:01.440 --> 00:10:03.720 align:middle line:10%
curious arrows pointing inward.

00:10:03.720 --> 00:10:06.600 align:middle line:10%
There's our three rays that
we talked about earlier once

00:10:06.600 --> 00:10:07.540 align:middle line:10%
again.

00:10:07.540 --> 00:10:12.340 align:middle line:84%
So what I decided to do is just
to take the God Particle logo,

00:10:12.340 --> 00:10:14.900 align:middle line:84%
superimpose it on top of
the Transfigured Jesus,

00:10:14.900 --> 00:10:16.042 align:middle line:90%
and what do you know?

00:10:16.042 --> 00:10:18.050 align:middle line:90%
It's just a perfect match.

00:10:18.050 --> 00:10:19.151 align:middle line:90%
That's just getting lucky.

00:10:19.151 --> 00:10:21.650 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't necessarily mean
that that's exactly what they're

00:10:21.650 --> 00:10:22.320 align:middle line:90%
talking about.

00:10:22.320 --> 00:10:24.556 align:middle line:84%
But hey, there's
more to come here.

00:10:24.556 --> 00:10:25.680 align:middle line:90%
We're just getting started.

00:10:25.680 --> 00:10:28.060 align:middle line:84%
We're just kind of starting
to piece little pieces here

00:10:28.060 --> 00:10:30.530 align:middle line:84%
together of this
puzzle that science

00:10:30.530 --> 00:10:33.800 align:middle line:84%
is presenting to us and the
symbolism that they chose.

00:10:33.800 --> 00:10:36.260 align:middle line:84%
In his book The God
Particle, Nobel laureate

00:10:36.260 --> 00:10:38.960 align:middle line:84%
and Fermilab director
Leon Lederman

00:10:38.960 --> 00:10:41.100 align:middle line:90%
writes, why the God Particle?

00:10:41.100 --> 00:10:42.140 align:middle line:90%
And he says two reasons.

00:10:42.140 --> 00:10:44.431 align:middle line:84%
One, the publishers wouldn't
let us call it the Goddamn

00:10:44.431 --> 00:10:48.700 align:middle line:84%
Particle, though that might be
a more appropriate title, given

00:10:48.700 --> 00:10:50.840 align:middle line:84%
its villainous nature
and the expense

00:10:50.840 --> 00:10:54.140 align:middle line:90%
it's causing, the frustration.

00:10:54.140 --> 00:10:57.390 align:middle line:84%
Lederman goes on to say that
there's a second reason why

00:10:57.390 --> 00:10:59.260 align:middle line:90%
we call it the God Particle.

00:10:59.260 --> 00:11:02.150 align:middle line:84%
And it refers to a much
older book, he said,

00:11:02.150 --> 00:11:04.200 align:middle line:84%
after which point
he connects the God

00:11:04.200 --> 00:11:06.230 align:middle line:84%
Particle, the search
for the God Particle,

00:11:06.230 --> 00:11:08.960 align:middle line:84%
to the story of
the Tower of Babel.

00:11:08.960 --> 00:11:10.530 align:middle line:84%
And what Lederman
essentially says

00:11:10.530 --> 00:11:14.840 align:middle line:84%
is that our search for this
and the discovery of the God

00:11:14.840 --> 00:11:17.440 align:middle line:84%
Particle would make the
universe more simple,

00:11:17.440 --> 00:11:21.700 align:middle line:84%
in essence undoing
the Tower of Babel.

00:11:21.700 --> 00:11:27.040 align:middle line:84%
Now, if scientists don't
want us to think like mystics

00:11:27.040 --> 00:11:30.110 align:middle line:84%
and put a metaphysical
spin on their work,

00:11:30.110 --> 00:11:34.400 align:middle line:84%
they just need to stop
doing stuff like this.

00:11:34.400 --> 00:11:38.040 align:middle line:84%
Because unless they want
us to think like this,

00:11:38.040 --> 00:11:40.320 align:middle line:90%
just stop this, OK?

00:11:40.320 --> 00:11:42.160 align:middle line:90%
Keep the two separate.

00:11:42.160 --> 00:11:44.590 align:middle line:84%
Now, Lederman says
that his publisher

00:11:44.590 --> 00:11:47.130 align:middle line:84%
put the title, The
God Particle, on it.

00:11:47.130 --> 00:11:48.860 align:middle line:84%
They put sexy titles
on these books,

00:11:48.860 --> 00:11:51.370 align:middle line:84%
and sometimes they
really don't mean it.

00:11:51.370 --> 00:11:54.000 align:middle line:84%
And here, he wrote
it himself, saying

00:11:54.000 --> 00:11:56.410 align:middle line:84%
that we want to think in
terms of the Tower of Babel

00:11:56.410 --> 00:11:58.906 align:middle line:84%
here when we're talking
about the God Particle.

00:11:58.906 --> 00:12:00.780 align:middle line:84%
So we'll just go with
him and say, all right.

00:12:00.780 --> 00:12:02.740 align:middle line:90%
Let's just ask the question.

00:12:02.740 --> 00:12:04.900 align:middle line:84%
Is the search for
the God Particle,

00:12:04.900 --> 00:12:07.630 align:middle line:84%
is the particle accelerator
at CERN as well as

00:12:07.630 --> 00:12:09.740 align:middle line:84%
the one at Fermilab
a reenactment

00:12:09.740 --> 00:12:12.340 align:middle line:84%
of the Babel incident when
humankind gathered together

00:12:12.340 --> 00:12:15.340 align:middle line:84%
to build a ladder or gate
that reached into the heavens?

00:12:15.340 --> 00:12:17.780 align:middle line:84%
Is that what we're
really doing here?

00:12:17.780 --> 00:12:20.280 align:middle line:84%
I think that's exactly
what we're doing here.

00:12:20.280 --> 00:12:22.731 align:middle line:10%
"Come, let us build ourselves
a city with a tower that

00:12:22.731 --> 00:12:24.480 align:middle line:10%
reaches to the heavens
so that we may make

00:12:24.480 --> 00:12:27.950 align:middle line:10%
a name for ourselves
and not be scattered

00:12:27.950 --> 00:12:29.910 align:middle line:10%
over the face of the earth."

00:12:29.910 --> 00:12:33.300 align:middle line:84%
That's what the book of Genesis
says about the Tower of Babel.

00:12:33.300 --> 00:12:36.290 align:middle line:84%
And ultimately, it also
said that if humankind

00:12:36.290 --> 00:12:40.230 align:middle line:84%
were successful in building
this God Particle detector--

00:12:40.230 --> 00:12:41.480 align:middle line:90%
excuse me, the Tower of Babel.

00:12:41.480 --> 00:12:43.230 align:middle line:84%
Well, I guess they're
interchangeable now,

00:12:43.230 --> 00:12:44.130 align:middle line:90%
aren't they?

00:12:44.130 --> 00:12:47.930 align:middle line:84%
Nothing they do will
be impossible to them.

00:12:47.930 --> 00:12:50.640 align:middle line:84%
This is why I say we're going
from cosmic kindergarten

00:12:50.640 --> 00:12:53.540 align:middle line:84%
to first grade,
cosmically speaking.

00:12:53.540 --> 00:12:57.120 align:middle line:84%
Because what we're doing
is the impossible here,

00:12:57.120 --> 00:12:59.690 align:middle line:84%
or what as here to before
been described as impossible.

00:12:59.690 --> 00:13:02.600 align:middle line:90%


00:13:02.600 --> 00:13:06.960 align:middle line:84%
By the way, one of the real
world spin-offs of the God

00:13:06.960 --> 00:13:10.170 align:middle line:84%
Particle is they've discovered
a technique whereby they can

00:13:10.170 --> 00:13:14.284 align:middle line:90%
zap fat cells with vibration.

00:13:14.284 --> 00:13:15.950 align:middle line:84%
And literally, they
believe that they're

00:13:15.950 --> 00:13:17.350 align:middle line:84%
going to be able to
create a technology,

00:13:17.350 --> 00:13:18.974 align:middle line:84%
you'll just be able
to stand in a room,

00:13:18.974 --> 00:13:21.560 align:middle line:84%
and your fat cells will just
simply be zapped away from you

00:13:21.560 --> 00:13:22.742 align:middle line:90%
and fall off.

00:13:22.742 --> 00:13:24.200 align:middle line:84%
That's a few years
away, but that's

00:13:24.200 --> 00:13:26.550 align:middle line:84%
one thing they say
for sure will drop out

00:13:26.550 --> 00:13:29.550 align:middle line:84%
of the research
they're doing at CERN.

00:13:29.550 --> 00:13:34.550 align:middle line:84%
Another is the Grid, which is
the new, souped up internet

00:13:34.550 --> 00:13:39.690 align:middle line:84%
that is 10,000 times faster
than the current internet.

00:13:39.690 --> 00:13:42.990 align:middle line:84%
The internet was
invented by the Air Force

00:13:42.990 --> 00:13:45.250 align:middle line:84%
as a communication
system that would be put

00:13:45.250 --> 00:13:47.510 align:middle line:90%
in place after a nuclear war.

00:13:47.510 --> 00:13:50.150 align:middle line:84%
The worldwide web
was invented at CERN

00:13:50.150 --> 00:13:52.560 align:middle line:84%
so that scientists
could share their data.

00:13:52.560 --> 00:13:55.920 align:middle line:84%
This Large Hadron
Collider at CERN

00:13:55.920 --> 00:13:59.100 align:middle line:84%
will spit out every
year the equivalent

00:13:59.100 --> 00:14:01.610 align:middle line:90%
of all of the data on Google.

00:14:01.610 --> 00:14:02.770 align:middle line:90%
Every year.

00:14:02.770 --> 00:14:06.860 align:middle line:84%
And so they needed a network
of computers, 100,000 computers

00:14:06.860 --> 00:14:09.960 align:middle line:84%
to be specific, that
will be designed

00:14:09.960 --> 00:14:12.210 align:middle line:84%
to help them unlock the
mysteries of the universe, one

00:14:12.210 --> 00:14:12.810 align:middle line:90%
thing.

00:14:12.810 --> 00:14:14.750 align:middle line:84%
And scientists believe
that this Grid, which

00:14:14.750 --> 00:14:17.660 align:middle line:84%
is described as a
worldwide revolution,

00:14:17.660 --> 00:14:20.300 align:middle line:84%
also has the capacity to
find a cure for cancer

00:14:20.300 --> 00:14:24.110 align:middle line:84%
and save lives following
a natural disaster.

00:14:24.110 --> 00:14:28.930 align:middle line:84%
It's hard for us to imagine an
internet 10,000 times faster

00:14:28.930 --> 00:14:31.816 align:middle line:84%
than what we've got presently
and the implications of that.

00:14:31.816 --> 00:14:32.940 align:middle line:90%
But just try to think back.

00:14:32.940 --> 00:14:36.360 align:middle line:84%
What was your life like in 1980
before there was the internet,

00:14:36.360 --> 00:14:38.250 align:middle line:90%
before you were online?

00:14:38.250 --> 00:14:38.990 align:middle line:90%
Very simple.

00:14:38.990 --> 00:14:40.191 align:middle line:90%
It was very different.

00:14:40.191 --> 00:14:41.690 align:middle line:84%
The Grid has already
been used, they

00:14:41.690 --> 00:14:43.370 align:middle line:84%
say, but is now more
powerful and has

00:14:43.370 --> 00:14:46.125 align:middle line:84%
been declared ready to deal
with the deluge of data that

00:14:46.125 --> 00:14:47.900 align:middle line:84%
will come from the
giant atom smasher

00:14:47.900 --> 00:14:50.376 align:middle line:90%
when it fires up next spring.

00:14:50.376 --> 00:14:51.750 align:middle line:84%
I thought it was
kind of humorous

00:14:51.750 --> 00:14:54.310 align:middle line:84%
that they've got on
this particular article

00:14:54.310 --> 00:14:58.430 align:middle line:84%
a photo of Steve Jobs down here
with his Apple behind them.

00:14:58.430 --> 00:14:59.940 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not
pinpointing Steve Jobs.

00:14:59.940 --> 00:15:02.840 align:middle line:84%
It's just the whole
computer industry is foaming

00:15:02.840 --> 00:15:07.310 align:middle line:84%
at the mouth right now about
how they can make you an iBod

00:15:07.310 --> 00:15:09.390 align:middle line:90%
and put you into that Grid.

00:15:09.390 --> 00:15:12.180 align:middle line:84%
That Grid will be damn near
artificially intelligent,

00:15:12.180 --> 00:15:14.013 align:middle line:84%
and you won't be able
to tell the difference

00:15:14.013 --> 00:15:16.530 align:middle line:84%
between that Grid and God by
the time they're done with it.

00:15:16.530 --> 00:15:20.200 align:middle line:84%
All our lives, everything
will be online and active.

00:15:20.200 --> 00:15:21.990 align:middle line:90%
You will be totally trackable.

00:15:21.990 --> 00:15:22.980 align:middle line:90%
You'll be chipped.

00:15:22.980 --> 00:15:24.020 align:middle line:90%
You'll be online.

00:15:24.020 --> 00:15:26.410 align:middle line:84%
They'll be able to enter your
consciousness at any time.

00:15:26.410 --> 00:15:28.220 align:middle line:84%
They'll be able to
tune your emotions,

00:15:28.220 --> 00:15:32.590 align:middle line:84%
good, bad, the ugly, at will,
whatever they want to do

00:15:32.590 --> 00:15:35.930 align:middle line:84%
And that is one of the
real-world implications

00:15:35.930 --> 00:15:40.780 align:middle line:84%
of this, perhaps the
scariest part of this.

00:15:40.780 --> 00:15:42.710 align:middle line:84%
At Yale, there was
an article yesterday

00:15:42.710 --> 00:15:46.280 align:middle line:84%
I saw on dailygalaxy.com
where researchers at Yale

00:15:46.280 --> 00:15:50.460 align:middle line:84%
have discovered how they can
derive enough electricity

00:15:50.460 --> 00:15:54.010 align:middle line:84%
to power these devices that
will be implanted in our skin

00:15:54.010 --> 00:15:57.270 align:middle line:84%
just by the electricity
coming off your cells.

00:15:57.270 --> 00:15:59.360 align:middle line:84%
So they finally figured
out, they believe,

00:15:59.360 --> 00:16:01.410 align:middle line:84%
how they can use the
body as the charging

00:16:01.410 --> 00:16:02.667 align:middle line:90%
system for these devices.

00:16:02.667 --> 00:16:04.000 align:middle line:90%
That was one of the big hangups.

00:16:04.000 --> 00:16:07.870 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, we can turn you into
an implant, a walking iBod,

00:16:07.870 --> 00:16:09.460 align:middle line:84%
but we need a power
source for it.

00:16:09.460 --> 00:16:10.520 align:middle line:84%
And they always
knew the body was

00:16:10.520 --> 00:16:12.436 align:middle line:84%
a tremendous source of
energy, and now they've

00:16:12.436 --> 00:16:13.930 align:middle line:90%
finally cracked that code, too.

00:16:13.930 --> 00:16:19.160 align:middle line:84%
So they're good to go, just
about, and ready to launch.

00:16:19.160 --> 00:16:21.160 align:middle line:84%
You're walking around
right now with a cellphone

00:16:21.160 --> 00:16:24.310 align:middle line:84%
that you go like this with,
or you put in the Bluetooth

00:16:24.310 --> 00:16:26.849 align:middle line:84%
in your ear, that's
going to start to recede.

00:16:26.849 --> 00:16:29.140 align:middle line:84%
You're going to be putting
your Bluetooth in your tooth

00:16:29.140 --> 00:16:30.380 align:middle line:90%
in a couple of years.

00:16:30.380 --> 00:16:31.810 align:middle line:90%
But that's intermediate.

00:16:31.810 --> 00:16:34.900 align:middle line:84%
Where they're aiming
for all of this

00:16:34.900 --> 00:16:37.610 align:middle line:84%
is human skin as
the next platform

00:16:37.610 --> 00:16:39.000 align:middle line:90%
for computer development.

00:16:39.000 --> 00:16:43.510 align:middle line:84%
They want to literally put a new
skin on you that is then wired

00:16:43.510 --> 00:16:47.380 align:middle line:90%
into this Grid, and off we go.

00:16:47.380 --> 00:16:50.210 align:middle line:90%
Having fun yet?

00:16:50.210 --> 00:16:53.160 align:middle line:84%
Here's today's internet
in this graphic

00:16:53.160 --> 00:16:56.342 align:middle line:84%
put out by the SyFy channel,
and here's the Grid.

00:16:56.342 --> 00:16:58.050 align:middle line:84%
I think it's kind of
humorous, because it

00:16:58.050 --> 00:17:00.065 align:middle line:90%
looks like a wormhole to me.

00:17:00.065 --> 00:17:02.565 align:middle line:84%
It really illustrates the idea
that what we've got right now

00:17:02.565 --> 00:17:09.170 align:middle line:84%
is just a tiny speck compared
to where all this is going.

00:17:09.170 --> 00:17:12.791 align:middle line:84%
CBS News, 60 Minutes went to
CERN just a couple of weeks

00:17:12.791 --> 00:17:13.290 align:middle line:90%
ago.

00:17:13.290 --> 00:17:15.500 align:middle line:90%
This is October 1, 2008.

00:17:15.500 --> 00:17:18.280 align:middle line:84%
The Grid went online
October 3, 2008.

00:17:18.280 --> 00:17:19.579 align:middle line:90%
So all this is really fresh.

00:17:19.579 --> 00:17:21.599 align:middle line:84%
This just happened in
the past few weeks.

00:17:21.599 --> 00:17:24.683 align:middle line:84%
Steve Kroft went to the Large
Hadron Collider for 60 Minutes,

00:17:24.683 --> 00:17:26.099 align:middle line:84%
because they have
a problem there.

00:17:26.099 --> 00:17:28.150 align:middle line:84%
They fired it up, then they
had to immediately shut down.

00:17:28.150 --> 00:17:29.447 align:middle line:90%
They had some kind of problem.

00:17:29.447 --> 00:17:30.780 align:middle line:90%
It had to shut down till spring.

00:17:30.780 --> 00:17:32.580 align:middle line:84%
So Steve Kroft went
there to investigate.

00:17:32.580 --> 00:17:33.400 align:middle line:90%
He say, hey.

00:17:33.400 --> 00:17:33.900 align:middle line:90%
What's up?

00:17:33.900 --> 00:17:34.997 align:middle line:90%
What's going on.

00:17:34.997 --> 00:17:36.580 align:middle line:84%
He had a conversation
with a physicist

00:17:36.580 --> 00:17:39.686 align:middle line:84%
named Bob Stanek, one of the
primary physicists at CERN.

00:17:39.686 --> 00:17:41.060 align:middle line:84%
And here's the
pertinent exchange

00:17:41.060 --> 00:17:43.190 align:middle line:90%
between Kroft and Stanek.

00:17:43.190 --> 00:17:45.630 align:middle line:84%
"Asked why scientists are
interested in recreating what

00:17:45.630 --> 00:17:48.880 align:middle line:84%
the universe was like a
nanosecond after the Big Bang,

00:17:48.880 --> 00:17:51.740 align:middle line:84%
Stanek tells Kroft,
'it's in humans' interest

00:17:51.740 --> 00:17:54.490 align:middle line:90%
to know everything, right?

00:17:54.490 --> 00:17:58.830 align:middle line:84%
And why wouldn't you want
to know that?'" Steve Kroft

00:17:58.830 --> 00:18:00.850 align:middle line:84%
responds, saying "Well,
you'd want to know it.

00:18:00.850 --> 00:18:03.670 align:middle line:84%
But, you know, spending
$8 billion to find out,

00:18:03.670 --> 00:18:06.200 align:middle line:90%
it must be important."

00:18:06.200 --> 00:18:08.580 align:middle line:84%
Stanek responds, "So, let
me ask you this question.

00:18:08.580 --> 00:18:10.910 align:middle line:84%
Because we've studied the
interactions of photons

00:18:10.910 --> 00:18:12.810 align:middle line:84%
and electrons in
elementary particles,

00:18:12.810 --> 00:18:15.910 align:middle line:84%
we can understand how to take
the light that bounces off me

00:18:15.910 --> 00:18:19.310 align:middle line:84%
and you into that camera,
and take that signal

00:18:19.310 --> 00:18:21.440 align:middle line:84%
and put it into mom
and pop's living room.

00:18:21.440 --> 00:18:26.810 align:middle line:84%
Now, imagine in 10 years, 20
years, will we be able to take,

00:18:26.810 --> 00:18:30.310 align:middle line:84%
instead of our
photons, me and you

00:18:30.310 --> 00:18:32.790 align:middle line:84%
and put them into mom
and pop's living room?

00:18:32.790 --> 00:18:37.080 align:middle line:84%
So you tell me,
is that worth it?"

00:18:37.080 --> 00:18:41.850 align:middle line:84%
That cracking sound was my
jaw hitting the floor, OK?

00:18:41.850 --> 00:18:44.110 align:middle line:90%
Steve Kroft, too.

00:18:44.110 --> 00:18:47.650 align:middle line:90%
"Transport people?"

00:18:47.650 --> 00:18:51.590 align:middle line:84%
Emphasis mine on the
incredulous response.

00:18:51.590 --> 00:18:52.190 align:middle line:90%
"You tell me.

00:18:52.190 --> 00:18:52.950 align:middle line:90%
Is that worth it?

00:18:52.950 --> 00:18:54.865 align:middle line:90%
Is that worth $8 billion?"

00:18:54.865 --> 00:18:57.259 align:middle line:90%
Stanek responds.

00:18:57.259 --> 00:18:58.800 align:middle line:84%
Asked if he thinks
that could happen,

00:18:58.800 --> 00:19:00.260 align:middle line:84%
Stanek replies,
well I don't know,

00:19:00.260 --> 00:19:03.000 align:middle line:84%
right now, I--
isn't it lunchtime?

00:19:03.000 --> 00:19:04.700 align:middle line:84%
I think I've said
too much already.

00:19:04.700 --> 00:19:06.360 align:middle line:84%
I better just buy
back everything

00:19:06.360 --> 00:19:08.640 align:middle line:84%
I said because I don't
want to sound like I'm

00:19:08.640 --> 00:19:12.070 align:middle line:84%
some crackpot physicist telling
you that within 10 to 20 years,

00:19:12.070 --> 00:19:14.620 align:middle line:84%
